  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Afghanistan has been in a state of protracted conflict for over 40 years compounding a high level of continued vulnerability across Afghan social fabric. According to the Fragile State Index, Afghanistan is in a state of high alert as ninth most fragile country in the world. In a population of estimated more than 37 million people, more than a third of the population is now in humanitarian need due to conflict, disaster and COVID-19</narrative>
